&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Principal AI Agent Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, you define what “great” looks like for agent engineering at Liberate. You set the technical bar, shape how we deploy AI at scale, and ensure we build leverage instead of heroics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You operate across customers, teams, and initiatives. You are trusted with the hardest problems, the messiest launches, and the highest-risk decisions. Your impact shows up not just in what you ship, but in how the organization gets stronger around you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the technical authority for agent architecture, quality, and deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the most complex and high-risk customer launches and recoveries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define standards for agent design, prompts, evals, monitoring, and launch readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify systemic gaps and drive solutions that reduce repeat incidents and toil&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Platform, Data Science, and Product to shape agent strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design reusable frameworks that turn customer work into durable platform leverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead by example in reviews, incidents, retros, and hard tradeoff decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor Staff and Senior engineers and raise the bar across the org&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
